cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DL 

The paper deals with analyzing news articles, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the evolution of stories, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses an algorithm to mine historical news data, which could fall under cs.DL (Machine Learning).
